&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Major Canal Irrigation projects of UP are as below:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eastern Yamuna Canal&lt;/strong&gt; -&amp;nbsp;Eastern Yamuna Canal, originates from the left bank of the Yamuna river from Tajevala. Through this canal system, the Hindon Yamuna Doab irrigation facility is provided to Saharanpur, Muzzafarnagar, Meerut, and Ghaziabad districts.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Upper Ganga Canal- &lt;/strong&gt;originates from Bheemgauda, Haridwar. Colonel Sir P.T. Kaatle was known as the father of this project. Through this canal system, the Irrigation facility is provided to Haridwar, Saharanpur, Muzzafarnagar, Meerut, Ghaziabad, Bulandshahr, Aligarh, Etah, Mathura, Firozabad, Mainpuri, and Agra districts.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agra Canal System&lt;/strong&gt;- originates from Noida to provide&amp;nbsp;Irrigation in Faridabad and Gurgaon districts of Haryana, in Mathura and Agra districts of Uttar Pradesh, and in Bharatpur district of Rajasthan.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sharda Canal System-&lt;/strong&gt; originates from Sharda River near Khatima, Nainital.&amp;nbsp;Nainital, Peelibhit, Bareily, Lakhimpur Kheiri, Shahjahanpur, Hardoi, Unnao, Lucknow, Barabanki, Raebareli, Pratapgarh, Sultanpur, Jaunpur, Azamgarh, Ghazipur, and Prayagraj districts are irrigated through it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
