&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gujarat and Kerala&lt;/strong&gt; were the 2&lt;sup&gt;nd&lt;/sup&gt; and 3&lt;sup&gt;rd &lt;/sup&gt;states respectively to implement it after Tamil Nadu.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On 15 Aug 1995, it was taken as a &lt;strong&gt;National scheme called &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (34, 34, 34);  &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nutrition Support to Primary Education Scheme or Mid-Day Meal program&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (34, 34, 34);  &quot;&gt;It was taken under by the MHRD ministry (In 2020 name was changed to Ministry of Education).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to the scheme, all the primary and upper primary students of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (34, 34, 34);  &quot;&gt;government schools and government-aided schools like Alternative and Innovative Education (AIE) centers and Madrasas will get free lunch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (34, 34, 34);  &quot;&gt;According to 2020 Ministry data over 11.9 Cr students are benefited from the scheme.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (34, 34, 34);  &quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://w.ndtvimg.com/sites/3/2019/12/21142100/tw81.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width: 350px; height: 196px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://w.ndtvimg.com/sites/3/2019/12/21141907/tw3.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width: 350px; height: 196px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ministry of Rural Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;is NOT associated with the initiative of&lt;strong&gt; Beti Bachao, Beti Padhao Scheme.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beti Bachao, Beti Padhao &lt;/strong&gt;is a Government of India initiative aimed at raising awareness and increasing the quality of child welfare programs in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was launched by&lt;strong&gt; PM Narendra Modi on&amp;nbsp;22 January 2015.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On 26 August 2016, the 2016 &lt;strong&gt;Olympics Bronze Medalist Sakshi Malik&lt;/strong&gt; was named BBBP Brand Ambassador.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is primarily targeted at regions in &lt;strong&gt;Uttar Pradesh, Haryana, Uttarakhand, Punjab, Bihar and Delhi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ministry of Health and Family Welfare,&amp;nbsp;Ministry of Women and Child Development and&amp;nbsp;Ministry of Human Resource Development has initiated this scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensuring continuous power supply to rural India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deen Dayal Upadhyaya Gram Jyoti Yojana (DDUGJY) was launched by Prime Minister Narendra Modi in Patna, Bihar. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The aim of this flagship scheme is to provide 24&amp;times;7 uninterrupted &lt;/strong&gt;electricity supply to each rural household across the country &lt;strong&gt;by 2022. DDUGJY has replaced Rajiv Gandhi Grameen Vidyutikaran Yojana (RGGVY),&lt;/strong&gt; which was launched by the &lt;strong&gt;previous UPA government led by then PM Manmohan Singh.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Objectives of DDUGJY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;To provide electricity to all villages.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Feeder separation to ensure sufficient power to farmers and regular supply to other consumers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Improvement of sub-transmission and distribution networks to improve the quality and reliability of the supply.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Metering to reduce the losses.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deen Dayal Upadhyaya Gram Jyoti Yojana (DDUGJY) &amp;ndash; Salient Features&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Separation of agriculture and non-agriculture feeders.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strengthening and augmentation of sub-transmission and distribution infrastructure in rural areas&lt;/strong&gt; including metering of distribution transformers feeders/consumers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rural electrification as per CCEA approval for completion of the targets laid down under RGGVY&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;To ensure &lt;strong&gt;rapid electrification, feeder separation&lt;/strong&gt;, and strengthening of rural distribution infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is necessary to &lt;strong&gt;monitor progress intensively&lt;/strong&gt; for smooth and fast implementation of electrification.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Government of India introduced Merchandise Exports from India Scheme (MEIS) through the &lt;strong&gt;Foreign Trade Policy (FTP) 2015-20 w.e.f. April 1, 2015.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It seeks to promote &lt;strong&gt;export of notified goods manufactured/ produced in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;It is implemented by the &lt;strong&gt;Ministry of Commerce and Industry&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Under this scheme, government&amp;nbsp;provides &lt;strong&gt;duty benefits at 2%, 3% and 5% &lt;/strong&gt;depending upon the product and country.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It has&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;three&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;sub components:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Vishesh Krishi and Gram Udyog Yojana&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Focus Market Scheme&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Focus Product Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Earlier there were &lt;strong&gt;5 different schemes&lt;/strong&gt; for rewarding merchandise exports with different kinds of duty scrips with varying conditions attached to their use and now they have been merged into MEIS.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Swayamsiddha&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Swayamsiddha Foundation&lt;/strong&gt; works in the field of Women Empowerment through various initiatives such as motivation, training, skill up-gradation, marketing, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It aids Women Empowerment through interventions in Self Employment and Self Help Groups (SHGs).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Self Employment:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Organizing Awareness Programmes on Self Employment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Organizing Skill Oriented Training Programmes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Providing Business Inputs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Providing Handholding Support.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Providing marketing platform for products of entrepreneurs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SHG (Bachat Gats):&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mentoring of New Groups.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strengthening of existing SHGs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Registering New &amp;amp; Existing Groups.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Addressing common problems of SHGs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Capacity Building of enrolled SHGs&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Imparting Training to enrolled SHGs&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Assisting SHGs in their endeavour to excel.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Inclusive education for the disabled at the secondary stage:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Centrally Sponsored I.E.D.S.S., The scheme aims to enable all students with disabilities completing eight years of elementary schooling an opportunity to complete four years of secondary schooling (classes IX to XII) in an inclusive and enabling environment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It provides educational opportunities and facilities to students with disabilities in the general education system at the secondary level (classes IX to XII) and supports the training of general school teachers to meet the needs of children with disabilities at the secondary level.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The objectives of the scheme will be to ensure that:&lt;/strong&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Every child with a disability will be identified at the secondary level and his educational need assessed&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Every student in need of aids and appliances, assistive devices, will be provided the same&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;All architectural barriers in schools are removed so that students with disability have access to classrooms, laboratories, libraries, and toilets in the school&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Each student with a disability will be supplied learning material as per her requirement&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;All general school teachers at the secondary level will be provided basic training to teach students with disabilities within a period of three to five years&amp;nbsp;Students with disabilities will have access to support services like the appointment of special educators, the establishment of resource rooms in every block&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Model schools are set up in every state to develop good replicable practices in inclusive education.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan (SSA) is the Government of India&amp;#39;s flagship programme for the achievement of Universalization of Elementary Education (UEE) in a time-bound manner, as mandated by the 86th amendment to the Constitution of India making free and compulsory Education to the Children of 6-14 years age group, a Fundamental Right.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;SSA is being implemented in partnership with State Governments to cover the entire country and address the needs of 192 million children in 1.1 million habitations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The programme seeks to open new schools in those habitations which do not have schooling facilities and strengthen existing school infrastructure through provision of additional classrooms, toilets, drinking water, maintenance grant and school improvement grants.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Existing schools with inadequate teacher strength are provided with additional teachers, while the capacity of existing teachers is being strengthened by extensive training, grants for developing teaching-learning materials and strengthening of the academic support structure at a cluster, block and district level.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;SSA seeks to provide quality elementary education including life skills. SSA has a special focus on girl&amp;#39;s education and children with special needs. SSA also seeks to provide computer education to bR&amp;amp;Dge the digital divide.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Right to Education:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act or Right to Education Act (RTE), is an Act of the Parliament of India enacted on 4 August 2009, which describes the modalities of the importance of free and compulsory education for children between 6 and 14 in India under Article 21a of the Indian Constitution.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Micro&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Micro&lt;/strong&gt; stands for micro enterprises, which are the primary focus of the MUDRA (Micro Units Development and Refinance Agency) Yojana.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MUDRA Yojana was launched by the Government of India to provide funding to the non-corporate, non-farm small/micro enterprises.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The scheme aims to support the growth and development of micro-enterprises in India by providing financial assistance up to Rs. 10 lakh.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MUDRA loans are categorized into three products: Shishu (covering loans up to Rs. 50,000), Kishor (covering loans above Rs. 50,000 and up to Rs. 5 lakh), and Tarun (covering loans above Rs. 5 lakh and up to Rs. 10 lakh).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The initiative is aimed at promoting entrepreneurship and employment generation at the grassroots level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MUDRA Bank&lt;/strong&gt; was established as a subsidiary of SIDBI (Small Industries Development Bank of India).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The scheme also focuses on providing financial literacy and credit counseling to micro-entrepreneurs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MUDRA Yojana is part of the Pradhan Mantri MUDRA Yojana (PMMY), which was launched on 8th April 2015.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It aims to achieve financial inclusion by extending credit to micro-businesses, which often face difficulties in accessing formal banking channels.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The scheme has been instrumental in empowering women entrepreneurs and promoting inclusive growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ministry of Tribal Affairs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Ministry of Tribal Affairs&lt;/strong&gt; announced the launch of the &amp;#39;Amazon Future Engineer Programme.&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This program aims to provide computer science education to students from underserved and underrepresented communities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It includes initiatives like coding classes, scholarships, and internships to help students build a future in technology.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The program is part of a broader effort to bridge the digital divide and ensure equitable access to technology education.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Ministry of Tribal Affairs&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for the overall development and welfare of scheduled tribes in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It implements various schemes and programs aimed at improving the socio-economic conditions of tribal communities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The ministry also focuses on education, health, and livelihood opportunities for the tribal population.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Collaboration with private organizations like Amazon helps in leveraging technology and resources for the benefit of these communities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &amp;#39;Amazon Future Engineer Programme&amp;#39; is one such initiative that aligns with the ministry&amp;#39;s goals of promoting education and skill development among tribal students.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open Network for Digital Commerce (ONDC)&lt;/strong&gt; is an initiative by the &lt;strong&gt;Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ONDC aims to promote open networks developed on open-sourced methodology, using open specifications and open network protocols, independent of any specific platform.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The initiative is aimed at democratizing digital commerce and moving it away from platform-centric models to an open-network model.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ONDC will help small retailers and merchants to access a much larger market, thereby enhancing their business opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT)&lt;/strong&gt; functions under the Ministry of Commerce and Industry.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;DPIIT is responsible for the formulation and implementation of promotional and developmental measures for the growth of the industrial sector, keeping in view the national priorities and socio-economic objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is also responsible for the overall industrial policy, facilitating and increasing investments in the manufacturing sector, and promoting ease of doing business.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The ONDC initiative is part of the broader aim to enhance digital inclusion and create a level playing field for all stakeholders in the digital commerce ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Uttar Pradesh&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;UP police introduces &lt;strong&gt;Trinetra app 2.0&lt;/strong&gt;, a digital platform revolutionizing crime prevention and investigation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The app integrates over &lt;strong&gt;9.32 lakh criminal records&lt;/strong&gt;, enabling frontline officers to swiftly identify suspects during security checks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UP DGP Prashant Kumar &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;ADG law and order Amitabh Yash&lt;/strong&gt; launched the app at DGP headquarters.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Trinetra app 2.0 can be used by all police personnel of Inspector rank and above, offering seamless accessibility via Android and iOS mobile applications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It provides comprehensive crime-related information including crime histories, FIR details, interrogation reports, audio recordings, photographs, rewards, incarceration details, and seizure records.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The app empowers law enforcement with facial recognition capabilities for swift suspect identification based on photographic data.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It includes audio-based search functionality for identifying criminals based on voice samples, particularly beneficial for cybercrime investigations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Trinetra 2.0 features Crime GPT for instant access to comprehensive information regarding criminals and criminal activities, streamlining investigative processes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;1306 crores&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ghaziabad-Meerut Corridor Regional Rapid Transit System&lt;/strong&gt; project is India&amp;rsquo;s first regional rapid transit system, which aims to provide high-speed trains for intercity commuting every 15 minutes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The project is expected to cost Rs 30,000 crore.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Provision of Rs ____ crores is allocated for the project in fiscal year 2023 -24.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The&amp;nbsp;Delhi-Meerut Regional Rapid Transit System&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is an&amp;nbsp;82.15 km long&amp;nbsp;rapid &lt;strong&gt;rail corridor that will connect Delhi, Ghaziabad and Meerut.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The project is being &lt;strong&gt;executed by the&amp;nbsp;National Capital Region Transport Corporation &lt;/strong&gt;(NCRTC)&amp;nbsp;and is expected to be completed by&amp;nbsp;June 2025&amp;nbsp;at a cost of&amp;nbsp;₹30,274 crore (US$3.8 billion).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The corridor &lt;strong&gt;will have&amp;nbsp;14 stations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;and two depots at Duhai and Modipuram.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The project&amp;rsquo;s first phase, or the 17 km long priority corridor from Sahibabad to Duhai, was inaugurated by Prime Minister Narendra Modi on&amp;nbsp;20 October 2023.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The entire corridor is &lt;strong&gt;expected to be operational by&amp;nbsp;June 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
